CLOVE WHOLE: Cloves are the rich, brown, dried, unopened flower buds of Syzygium aromaticum, an evergreen tree in the myrtle family. The name comes from the French "clou" meaning nail. Cloves are native to the Molucca Islands, now a part of Indonesia and also from Madagascar and Sri Lanka. In addition to their sweet, aromatic flavour, cloves are known for their potent medicinal properties, some of which include aiding in digestion, boosting the immune system, controlling diabetes, and preserving bone quality. title: Clove Bud Floral Water 100ml (Hydrosol) 100% Pure And Natural
description:
Clove Bud Hydrosol

 Botanical Name : Eugenia caryophyllata

 Parts Used: Buds

 Extraction Method: Steam Distilled Hydrosol

 Appearance : Clear colorless to slightly cloudy liquid

 Odour: Warm, sweet-spicy, woody characteristic odour 

 DESCRIPTION:

 Hydrosols, also known as floral waters, hydroflorates, flower waters or distillates are products from steam distilling plant materials. Hydrosols are like essential oils but in far less of a concentration. When a distiller brews plant material with water in a large cooker the steam fills the pot and, as it rises, it causes the glands of the plants to burst and release the oils and essence of the plant into the steam. The oil rises through a condenser and collects in a separate vessel. This is what we know as essential oil, but what about all that fragrant water that was steamed with the original plant material? That is our hydrosol, or floral water. 

 APPLICATION:

 Our hydrosols can be used in toners, creams, lotions, body sprays, room sprays and in place of water in most formulations. The hydrosol will impart both fragrance and therapeutic benefits to your products. Hydrosols are also wonderful when used as wetting agents in clay facials. Floral waters are an exceptional way to enjoy the benefits of essential oils in a water soluble product.
